The paper also discusses the identification of inheritance and subtyping in OOP, which suggests that it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of domain theory to model partial information and higher-order computation, which suggests that it may belong to the Theory of Computation (cs.TP) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of domain constructors, which suggests that it may also belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
